Jan 22
He that pities another remembers himself.

Jan 23
He that is angry without a cause, must me satisfied without amends.

Jan 24
One pair of heels is often worth two pairs of hands.

Jan 25
A blind man will not thank you for a looking glass.

Jan 26
A gift with a kind countenance is a double present.

Jan 27
Be ever at leisure to do good; never make business your excuse to decline the works of humanity.

Jan 28
Discontents do arise from our desires oftener than from our needs.

Jan 29
Good jests bite like lambs, not like dogs.

Jan 30
It is better to decide an argument between enemies than friends; for one friend will certainly become an enemy and one enemy a friend.

Feb 1
He that riseth late, must trot all day, and shall scarce overtake his business at night.
